Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.74,0:00:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rhythm of the wind clarifies all reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.58,0:00:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and causes alibi tricks to fall apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.62,0:00:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the Three Kingdoms conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.12,0:00:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,these two sharp wits will extinguish the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.79,0:00:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.79,0:00:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.80,0:01:48.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori, Uncle and I returned to the Morozumi house, only to find that a fire had erupted...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.85,0:01:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and claimed Morozumi Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as its victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.35,0:01:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, from the ruins of the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.23,0:01:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,red horse figurine, similar to the ones at the other serial arson sites, was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.77,0:02:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after Genda Takanori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} confessed, it seemed as though the case had been solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.83,0:02:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Red Horse within the Flames,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.87,0:02:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conclusion Part!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.96,0:02:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! This is bad. It's already 3:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.09,0:02:25.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like we'll have to forget Tropical Land, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.30,0:02:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.10,0:02:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If what this boy said is true, then it's definitely possible to set fire to the house without being present.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.48,0:02:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, you should consider the fact that the burn marks on that bulb could've been caused by something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, with that method, couldn't any of those three have started the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.12,0:02:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morozumi Akira owns the house, so it's obvious why he'd fall under suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.83,0:03:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soga Misao was having an affair behind Ryoko's back, and Gondo Keiko frequently visited the house to ask for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.22,0:03:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we came all the way to Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house to find clues leading to the culprit, so let's hurry inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.10,0:03:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.22,0:03:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might find his diary or something else that's crucial to the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.11,0:03:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I'm really surprised that you got the key to his house without a warrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.95,0:03:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I told Genda I would prove his innocence, he handed it to me between bursts of tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.87,0:03:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, isn't this house too big for Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to live in all by himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he told me that he moved here so he could take care of his mother after his father passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.13,0:03:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That went on for about a year, until his mother passed away as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.26,0:03:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Mouri, did you notice this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.09,0:03:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ash on the floor by the guest room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there are a bunch of shoe prints scattered around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.68,0:04:00.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder who made them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.89,0:04:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.90,0:04:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They match perfectly with the shoe in the shoe rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.57,0:04:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really did suffer from...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.99,0:04:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There're some strange things in the trash can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.08,0:04:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pair of muddy socks and a partially burnt shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s sleepwalking condition was severe enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.88,0:04:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,his so-called "other personality" might actually have caused him to set the houses on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.80,0:04:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He isn't that kind of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.84,0:04:39.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not the type who would set fires to others' homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.81,0:04:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuminaga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, take a look at this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check out this phone bill I found on top of the shoe rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.66,0:04:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He spent 30,000 yen in a month!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that's a little excessive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.87,0:05:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While that's strange for a single man living by himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.54,0:05:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran spends that much on long calls to Sonoko, talking about stupid girlie nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.46,0:05:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm... Now that you mention it, Kazuha does the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.34,0:05:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She calls up my Mom and they blab on and on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.01,0:05:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why women like to talk on the phone so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.73,0:05:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, excuse us...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.73,0:05:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For making long, stupid phone calls!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.98,0:05:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.24,0:05:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you two were standing by the entrance, eavesdropping on us this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way we'd sink that low!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The car radio just started playing your voices for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.21,0:05:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.60,0:06:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this ceramics piece, there might be a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.64,0:06:03.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.89,0:06:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it! It's a listening device.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.56,0:06:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it! It's a listening device.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.06,0:06:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That thing... Isn't it the same type of vase that was by the entryway at Moruzumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.90,0:06:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, we heard some other things too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.86,0:06:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about a trash can...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.53,0:06:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be here! Somewhere near this trash can, another listening device has to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A crystal ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori, I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.13,0:06:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was inside the cushion of this crystal ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.80,0:06:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've seen one of those before!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.18,0:06:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fortune-teller was selling the same crystal balls at the convention across from Haido Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.52,0:06:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear her fortune-telling is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, doesn't that cushion look awfully similar to the one Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was holding?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.66,0:07:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.24,0:07:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...that something's in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.58,0:07:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.21,0:07:13.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.84,0:07:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't a listening device.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.76,0:07:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of that, we found something unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.85,0:07:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, a man named Genda turned himself in, but stopped talking right afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.98,0:07:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did confess to making the red horse figurines that were left at all of the fires...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.40,0:07:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he refuses to confess to starting all of those fires as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.28,0:07:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We came to his house to look for evidence, but we haven't been able to find anything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.03,0:07:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His story about sleepwalking and setting fires while unconscious seems pretty fabricated to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm sure forensics will find something when they come tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll contact you again if we make any progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.34,0:08:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, was that good enough, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.05,0:08:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were A-OK, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.72,0:08:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.43,0:08:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you ask him to lie to the three suspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.69,0:08:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't those all lies?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.06,0:08:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found listening devices planted on both the vase and the cushion for the crystal ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.78,0:08:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there are signs all over the place that prove Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sleepwalking!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.16,0:08:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'll explain everything later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.62,0:08:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, won't us being here interrupt the work of the forensics team?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.92,0:08:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah,yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.13,0:08:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our hair strands must be all over this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.79,0:08:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how would you go about covering our tracks?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.80,0:08:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the only way to just thoroughly scrub everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if you didn't have that much time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.81,0:08:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.42,0:11:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.67,0:11:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you forgetting to place this red horse somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arsonist{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.06,0:11:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or should I say...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.03,0:11:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morozumi Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.36,0:11:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The red horse key holder that Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made is what set this all in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.95,0:12:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This good luck charm of the red hare, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know the cause of the first fire in Rizen,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.09,0:12:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the red horse was only found because the owners of the house are some of Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s best customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.84,0:12:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably gave them one of these boxed key holders as an advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.85,0:12:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the fire spread before the box had been opened,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.85,0:12:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,burning both the box and Guan Yu, and leaving only the red hare behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.06,0:12:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the victims truthfully testified that they hadn't seen the horse before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.23,0:12:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police's codename for arsonists is "Red Hare," because it's read as "arsonist" in kana.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That caused the mass media to jump to the conclusion that a serial arsonist placed the horse there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.20,0:12:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was quite shocked that the victims didn't know about the horse in the key holder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.54,0:12:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was certain that he'd given it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he visited your psychiatric clinic, thinking his childhood sleepwalking habits had returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.93,0:12:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you realized Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s condition, you manipulated him into thinking he was a sleepwalking pyromaniac.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.56,0:13:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the first fire was on the 1st block, after burning down houses on a 2nd and 3rd block,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.61,0:13:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you set fire to your own house on the 4th block, killing your cheating wife, Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.40,0:13:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, removing the base and Guan Yu from the key holder, you left a red horse at each scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.28,0:13:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,effectively creating the illusion that a serial arsonist started the fires, and ultimately framing Genda for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.08,0:13:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You somehow got a spare key to this house, and snuck in night after night to mentally stress Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.59,0:13:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made shoe prints and left behind a burnt shirt and muddy socks to make him believe he was the arsonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.01,0:13:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But, Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came to my clinic of his own accord, since he was concerned about his sleepwalking habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.02,0:13:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.11,0:13:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had that problem during his childhood, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.61,0:13:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched a TV show that said it's common for kids to remain excited from playing as they sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.65,0:14:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,making them walk around while unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.20,0:14:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A professional psychiatrist such as yourself should know at least that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.37,0:14:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} being near my house the day it was set on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm his psychiatrist, but I couldn't have made him go there...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.22,0:14:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were listening in on Genda and Soga's conversations, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.22,0:14:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used the listening device you just retrieved from the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.35,0:14:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew he would visit, since he was trying to make his luck as a salesman improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you chose that day to carry out your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.03,0:14:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you switched the manekineko key holder he was supposed to hand out,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you knew he would notice and return to his clients' houses to exchange them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such odd behavior would make him seem suspicious to the neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had also asked a detective to come, which would give you an even more reputable witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.55,0:15:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Please, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time of the arson was just after 7:30 PM, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.10,0:15:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I left my house before 7:30 PM to go drinking with Sogaâ€”his testimony proves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.23,0:15:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or are you saying that the boy next door is lying about the time of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.44,0:15:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le... What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.91,0:15:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a tissue wrapped around and taped to this lightbulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.70,0:15:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, there's something stuck in the tissue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.87,0:15:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.29,0:15:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.13,0:15:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The surface temperaure of a 100 watt light bulb is 218 degrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.50,0:15:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should know what happens when you wrap a tissue around it and stick a match inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.97,0:15:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, you set this up so it would ignite and start the fire while you were out drinking with Soga{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.35,0:15:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the same method on the bulb in the storage room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.98,0:16:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you poured oil on the floor, placed the red horse on the windowsill, and turned on the light just before you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.87,0:16:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About 10 minutes later, the match ignited and burned the tissue, which fell onto the floor and started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.91,0:16:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, if the boy next door was watching TV in the dark as he usually did,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.84,0:16:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he'd see the shadow of the horse cast onto the curtain by the flames that spread from the tissue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.92,0:16:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would take a short amount of time to be made visible, as though the arsonist had just put it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.52,0:16:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You intended to erase any possible evidence that could be used against you, but we still have proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.86,0:16:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the base of the key holder that Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was holding in her hand when she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.36,0:16:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It matched perfectly with the legs of the horse found at the third block.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.45,0:16:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we need to do now is to compare the fingerprints on this to yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.37,0:16:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason you removed Guan Yu and the base was to keep anyone from finding out that Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.80,0:17:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you couldn't let him get arrested before you had the chance to kill Ryoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.64,0:17:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had already caught onto you, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.77,0:17:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She called a detective because there was a suspicious person sneaking around her house at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.48,0:17:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably you, testing your method outside the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.90,0:17:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have searched your room and found the red horses and base plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.95,0:17:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when she realized you were the arsonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.08,0:17:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what I can tell, she probably chased us away because...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.42,0:17:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.17,0:17:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was pressuring me for a divorce and planning to kick me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.17,0:17:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was only burning down the house to make room for my own clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.18,0:17:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.72,0:17:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only the base plate wasn't found...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I didn't fall for this trap...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.81,0:17:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been the perfect crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.27,0:17:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, we knew you were the culprit before you set foot in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.44,0:18:01.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie! You said that Soga and Ryoko's sister also...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.82,0:18:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, those two also sold items with listening devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.41,0:18:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They did this to convince Genda of their Feng Shui and fortune-telling abilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.29,0:18:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and sell their services to him at greatly increased prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.79,0:18:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, we were able to figure out that there was a listening device in the phone by looking at his phone bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.59,0:18:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you tap a phone line, the line stays connected all the time, causing the bill to skyrocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.89,0:18:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how did you know that I was the one who planted it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.27,0:18:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since those two also had listening devices, either one of them could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.44,0:18:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to tap a phone with a listening device, you need to get into the house first, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.36,0:18:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.74,0:18:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was one of theirs, wouldn't they have retrieved the device from what they sold him once they broke in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.12,0:19:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, if Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} found it, they'd be exposed as the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.34,0:19:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably came up with this plan after reading Agatha's Christie's The ABC Murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.39,0:19:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that's the case, why didn't you realize this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.22,0:19:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how well you plan a crime, the criminal never gets the last laugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.44,0:19:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's always the man who uses his little grey cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.54,0:19:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, see you, Mouri. Thanks for all the help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.29,0:19:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.13,0:19:49.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I should be thanking these kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.26,0:19:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what are you going to do with those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.81,0:20:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since they didn't intend to cause any harm,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.94,0:20:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they only came to retrieve their listening devices before they were wrongfully accused,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.11,0:20:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll give them a good lecture, and let them off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.61,0:20:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aside from that, why did you continue to believe in Genda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.12,0:20:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name came up during the investigation, so I decided to question him when I found him in a nearby park.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.71,0:20:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We sat silently on the bench for thirty minutes, so I gave up and told him we d talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.47,0:20:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I looked back at him, he was desperately searching for something in the grass near the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.22,0:20:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started to rain shortly after that, so he stopped searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.65,0:20:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw an expression of relief on his face, I finally understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.61,0:20:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd been looking for the cigarette that I'd dropped...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.24,0:20:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...the cause of the fire that took his father's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.83,0:21:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't even want to consider the possibility that such a man could set fire to other people's homes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.09,0:21:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.38,0:21:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you later, Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.31,0:22:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you give us little more of a discount?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.40,0:22:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially since we came all the way here to cheer you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.32,0:23:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But, that clock is the work of a famous artist!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.28,0:23:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.08,0:23:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock's hands don't even move, so it's not even useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.66,0:23:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.75,0:23:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, but you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.25,0:23:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.63,0:23:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll add this in if you make it a 500 yen discount. How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.88,0:23:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, if we don't hurry, we won't make it in time for our return flight!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.51,0:23:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, Uncle... I'll make this quick and simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.31,0:23:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.31,0:23:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.73,0:23:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about the discount...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.60,0:23:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can just give us this antique jewelery instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.11,0:23:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.23,0:23:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.82,0:23:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't do that, no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.61,0:23:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys... Are you actually trying to cheer him up?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.99,0:23:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're begging you, Uncle!
